textsBain Capital VI Coinvestment Fund LP 2009 Audited Financial Statements    



 by
Gawker.com
 


        Publication date 2012-08-07


        Topics documentcloud, gawker, 3346-john-cook 
 Collection
documentcloud; additional_collections



 Contributor
John Cook (Gawker.com )


 Language
English
 

Bain Capital VI Coinvestment Fund LP is a Delaware limited partnership principally engaged, according to its audited financial statements, with investing "in certain transactions concurrently with Bain Capital Fund VI LP," which Romney has disclosed a partnership stake in. The coinvestment fund shares a general partner--Bain Capital Partners VI LP--with Bain Capital Fund VI.

As of September 2010, the fund held $58.6 million in assets and reported a $40.5 million increase in capital for the nine months ended September 30, 2010.

The 2010 returns of both the Ann and Mitt Romney 1995 Family Trust and the Ann D. Romney Blind Trust report income from the general partner.
(Unofficial mirror of http://www.documentcloud.org/documents/407728-bain-capital-vi-coinvestment-fund-lp-financial.html)



