textsBain Capital VII Coinvestment Fund LP 2009 Audited Financial Statements    



 by
Gawker.com
 


        Publication date 2012-08-07


        Topics documentcloud, gawker, 3346-john-cook 
 Collection
documentcloud; additional_collections



 Contributor
John Cook (Gawker.com )


 Language
English
 

The Bain Capital VII Coinvestment Fund LP is a limited partnership based in the Cayman Islands. It shares a general partner with the Bain Capital Fund VII, LP, which Romney has disclosed a partnership stake in, and is, according to its audited financial statements, designed to "invest...in certain transactions concurrently with Bain Capital Fund VII LP." 

As of 2009, it held $141 million in assets and reported a $4 million decrease in capital.

In 2011, according to financial disclosures, the Ann D. Romney Blind Trust held between $100,000 and $250,000 in the coinvestment fund, earning between $100,000 and $1 million.
(Unofficial mirror of http://www.documentcloud.org/documents/407729-bain-capital-vii-coinvestment-fund-lp-financial.html)



